rComments: When I came into this semester, I was worried to have her as a prof due to the bad reviews on here. To my surprise, it wasn't that bad. She did have three proctored midterms that required a lot of studying, but the tested content was fair and similar to problem sets. She also gave extra marks for midterm 1 and 2. Make sure to study hard though.

okay so i didnt attend any lectures after the first three weeks cuz the slides are dry and she doesnt rlly explain anything clearly anyway. the only reason i did well in this class was cuz of the TA named tiffany. she did such a good job going over the problem sets in the DGD. i would take a class w tiffany, but not the actual prof again :)

Prof improved, but still one of the worst teachers I have ever had. She barely explains concepts and just reads off slides (already contain little info). DR. Musgaard was excellent throughout the course and provided fair midterms. Everyone giving the bad reviews are just upset about the Online final that was planned to prevent group work. Make the tests/exams MUCH SHORTER

first two midterms were representative of class material, but very long. Third midterm was way too long (13 pages) and much harder than her lectures and practice sets. Prof is monotone, however she is nice and approachable.
LONGEST EXAMS EVER!!! They never end

Yes her lectures may not be the most engaging but her grading criteria is very clear which is really what matters at the end of the day.
